                            <comment id="16451540" author="yucai" created="Wed, 25 Apr 2018 02:45:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;shuffle.partition = 8192&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12920562/12920562_p1.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;shuffle.partition = 8000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12920563/12920563_p2.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16451727" author="yucai" created="Wed, 25 Apr 2018 06:27:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The query example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-sql&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;insert&lt;/span&gt; overwrite &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;table&lt;/span&gt; target_xxx
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt;
 item_id,
 auct_end_dt
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt;
 (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;select&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;cast&lt;/span&gt;(item_id &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; item_id, auct_end_dt &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;from&lt;/span&gt;&#160;source_xxx
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt;
 item_id,
 auct_end_dt
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16451728" author="yucai" created="Wed, 25 Apr 2018 06:31:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Root cause: very bad hash conflict in hashaggregate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12920586/12920586_image-2018-04-25-14-29-39-958.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16451743" author="yucai" created="Wed, 25 Apr 2018 06:56:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1. When shuffle.partition = 8192, tuples in the same partition follows the connection like below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;hash(tuple x) = hash(tuple y) + n * 8192&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. In the next HashAggregate stage, tuples from the same partition&#160;need put into a 16K BytesToBytesMap (unsafeRowAggBuffer).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here, the HashAggregate uses the same hash algorithm and seed as shuffle, it leads to all tuples will be hashed to only 2 different places actually. That&apos;s why hash conflict happens.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16451753" author="apachespark" created="Wed, 25 Apr 2018 07:14:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;yucai&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/21149&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/21149&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
